<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy" effectiveDate="2026-05-10" appName="SnipSnaps">
  <p>
    SnipSnaps is a photo review app developed by Kyter, LLC. SnipSnaps is designed to help
    you review and clean up photos on your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Collection</h2>
  <p>SnipSnaps does not collect personal data.</p>
  <p>
    The app does not use third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, tracking SDKs, or account
    systems. SnipSnaps does not upload your photos to a server.
  </p>

  <h2>Photo Library Access</h2>
  <p>
    SnipSnaps asks for access to your photo library so it can show photos for review sessions
    and help you delete photos you explicitly choose to remove.
  </p>
  <p>
    Photo review and similar-photo grouping happen on device. When you confirm deletion,
    SnipSnaps uses Apple&rsquo;s Photos API to move selected photos to Recently Deleted.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>SnipSnaps does not sell, rent, share, or transfer your photo library data.</p>

  <h2>Network Use</h2>
  <p>SnipSnaps does not require an internet connection for its core photo review features.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    SnipSnaps is not directed to children under 13, and Kyter, LLC does not knowingly collect
    personal information from children through SnipSnaps.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    This privacy policy may be updated if SnipSnaps changes how it handles data. Updates will
    be posted on this page.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact Kyter, LLC at
    <a href="mailto:dev@kyter.com">dev@kyter.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
